caption: Tried this place in the past with my friend and I am obsessed since then. I like the awesome character and delicious food and beverages. Keep up the good work.

Top notch! I had passed on trying this place because there's no good place to order online, but finally stopped by in person for take out. Their menu is extensive and full of what you expect from a proper sushi bar.  The service was enthusiastically friendly and helpful. Whoever was at the door deserves a raise.  The sushi is *excellent* and I cannot stress that enough. Flavorful, well made, and proper proportions. I splurged on the O'o Toro sushi and was not disappointed.  Highly recommend. It's worth the stop.
I like this place very much. theres a happy mood. The kitcen is exeptionaly good. the service is effective and the team is courteous. The pay is satisfactory. truly recommend.
Awesome awesome awesome if you are in the area this is a must visit place for sushi
Great, high quality, no-frills sushi at reasonable prices.
This place never fails to deliver. They have fresh food for fair prices, there is no waiting time even when the spot is packed.
Great take out sushi. Easy ordering and pick up.
I don’t you believe can do better in the DMV.  They seem to have an inside track on getting the best fish.  Really lucky to have them near our place.
One of my main places to grab some food. convenient location, well organised, and very good service. I highly recommend them!

This spot is my favorite. I go to plenty of restaurants but to this restaurant I keep coming back again and again. The team is very professional and the cuisine they serve is so flavorful. I never decline to have a decent dinner in this restaurant. I recommend this place with pleasure.
Good sushi.

I order take out from here at least once a month (probably more during these quarantine times). I typically get the Sushi Gold (and a spicy yellowtail roll) and I’ve never been disappointed. The fish is always super fresh and the flavors are incredible. The staff is super kind - I love the cute messages on the take out bags!
Fresh, flavorful

12/11/2018...still excellent. Also their treatment for birthdays is wonderful, highly recommend. 10/2017: The omakase is a steal its price. The space is small and intimate, perfect for dates or small groups. Wait staff and sushi bar chefs were all excited for me to try their food but were not overbearing. The chefs certainty showed pride in their work.
Fantastic sushi, esp the Toro, Black Snapper and Gindara. Small intimate atmosphere. Best on the hill.
Great hidden sushi spot with chef's choice and regular offerings. Chefs' knifework is fantastic and the dishes reflect their skills fully.
This place is simply awesome! Totally worth the visit!!
LOVE THIS SPOT. SO SO WORTH IT!
Fantastic sushi and great service.
Delicious and hospitable. Loved it!
Everything was great! The staff were friendly, accommodating. Best spot around this neighborhood.

I adore this spot! They provide high class meals, they have a rich menu, The cook in that spot is a real authority in the kitchen, I love very much tasting all their dishes. The dishes are always good, the service towards the clients  is agreeable. I often go to  this restaurant and I was never unhappy.  I highly recommend it.
The BEST sushi I’ve tried in the DC area! Excellent Japanese beers as well.

Great fresh sashimi. The waitress was friendly and nice. There was a manager walking around and seemed to acknowledge everyone except our table. Not sure if he wasn't thrilled that we had a baby. Overall a good place and hopes that the manager treat all clients with respect and acknowledgement.
Very good sushi...great staff, no alcohol tho...I wanted some saki. However a very good spot for a quiet first date
Excellent sushi at reasonable prices.
Meal was flat lacking a sense of depth to the sushi
Thought it was pricy as but if you want flavoursome, authentic-tasting Japanese cuisine then this is a worthwhile visit.
This is a nice spot for sushi. It is not cheap but it’s good sushi.

Very impressed with this super cozy (seats around 10 people) restaurant.  My wife travels a lot for work (NY, LA) and is very picky about her sushi.  She loved this place.  Omakase and hand rolls were amazing!

We had the pleasure of dining in for lunch over the weekend. Some of the best sushi I’ve had.  We ordered the Omakase for lunch at $50 p/person and sat at the sushi bar. I enjoyed my experience as my sushi was prepared by the chef and serve directly to me at the bar. I didn’t take any pictures of the omakase because I didn’t want to be one of those that cant put their phone down. We had over 10 slices of sushi. Our meal came with Side dishes to complement the sushi.  Friendly staff and knowledgeable sushi chef!
Nice quiet place .great food . No alcohol though
The sushi is terrific, the service is excellent. This is a great place to go

I had been a big fan of sushi capitol. Haven’t been there for almost a year because being pregnant. And we just dined in and left the place with a huge disappointment and will no longer be there again. The quality of fish went downhill significantly. Always had omakase sushi and this time the fish assortment was cheap and the quality of the fish, esp tuna belly (otoro) and salmon, were bad (hard to chew as opposed to soft and melt to mouth as normally are). And no liquor served (or allowed to bring byob) as they said haven’t renewed liquor license, which was not disclosed at the time of me making a dinner reservation over the phone. And the manager didn’t give an apology for that. We saw a group of ppl were leaving after finding out they don’t serve alcoholic beverages. The waiting staff confirmed with us that they were separated from the sister restaurant sushi ogawa about 6 months ago and the management has been changed, and that probably the reason why the restaurant is going downhill.
The sushi is delicious. The people that work there are great. If you're getting sushi in this neighborhood then go here.
By far the best sushi in DC. Perfect service too.
Very quaint, with an emphasis on quality ingredients and attention to detail.

Definitely the best sushi fish I've ever had. They really care about quality and sourcing. Owner was incredibly friendly, interesting, and accommodating. Get the striped jack nigiri. Omakase was well worth it.

Awesome sushi! What made it even better was awesome service that we received from the server at lunch time on Aug 12. He wss so detail oriented and sincere. The best service since I moved out from Japan 15 years ago!
Very fresh and tasty!
This little find in Chinatown is amazing! Best sushi we’ve ever had. Pricey but so worth it.
The best sushi in the DC metro area as far as I can tell. Been coming here to celebrate and eat since 2015. Small space, get reservations.
Better sushi than in Japan!
They serve only water with no alcohol or other beverages.
Wish this place was bigger....reservations recommended or go when they first open.
Recently redone and looks great. Top it off with the best sushi in DC. Dont miss out on this place!!
Amazing!

Always great quality fish and fantastic service. We usually come here to splurge on the good stuff (omakase is the way to go), but it's also great that there are more affordable options too. We'll be back...
Really love it! Must go!
Took my daughter there for a birthday treat of some faves.  Absolutely delicious!  Also, they offer take out/ call ahead service as well.  Best sushi place I've been to in DC.

(Translated by Google) The salmon was delicious. There is no alcohol. Anyway, it was too early for the food to come out. At 18:00, I ordered 2 kinds of tempura, sashimi, sushi, 3 kinds of sushi rolls, but at 18:50, the clerk talks to the customer that this seat will be released soon, pointing his finger The feeling was bad.  (Original) 鮨は美味しかったです。アルコールはありません。とにかく料理が出てくるのが早かったです。18:00開始で天ぷら2種類、刺身、鮨人数分、巻き寿司3種類をオーダーしましたが、18:50分には、店員さんがお客さんにこの席がもうすぐ空くからと指を指して話していたのは、感じが悪かったです。
Recently renovated, always good, and very friendly, they do close on the early side.
Nice intimate setting with great sushi. Never disappoints
Great sushi.
Great fresh sushi for a reasonable price.
Excellent experience and very good sushi. Did the Sushi and Sashimi plates. Expensive but what I would expect from comparable sushi in another city. Will be back again.
Great sushi. Great price

Sushi Capitol is very small but what they lack in size they have in flavor big and bold and fresh and there prices are reasonable I just wish they had things to drink but this place still gets 5 stars from me.

Wow! Best sushi I've had in the US and at least as good as most of the places I went to when I lived in Japan. Service was great. Sushi was super fresh. All of the fish was amazing. Best uni I've had since I was last in Japan. Best anago I e ever had. I've been to all of the top sushi places in DC and this one, by far, is the top one.  I highly recommend Sushi Capitol. I cannot wait to visit Sushi Capitol again!
Best hidden sushi spot in D.C.
Amazing, hidden gem
One of the best I've tried so far!
Best sushi in DC!
This is hands down the best Sushi in Dc. I cannot get enough
The highest quality and most authentic sushi restaurant in D.C
The sushi was very fresh. Honestly, I expected better from all of the rave reviews, it seems that sushi in DC isn't as strong as other big cities.

Yummy sushi. Their salad was seaweed salad, didn't realise until the waiter brought it out, they very kindly allow me to return it. Prawn dumplings were more like prawn balls, not what I expected but it's delicious.
Potentially the best sushi in DC!

(Translated by Google) The sushi is good, even if the rice is not perfect. The service in short ... The very kind waitress, but the other type a curmudgeon who makes you pass the desire to dine .... He seems to be looking forward to seeing you go away.  (Original) Il sushi buono, anche se il riso non perfetto. Il servizio insomma... La cameriera gentilissima, ma l'altro tipo un musone che ti fa passare la voglia di cenare.... Sembra non veda l'ora di vederti andare via.
I hate to write this review since I loved this restaurant but the quality of omakase has changed. Also spotting a huge roach in the dining area didn’t help my appetite.
High quality sushi and great service
Good food, good sake, good services

Omakase in DC without breaking your bank. Really experienced chefs with highly skilled sourcing, cutting, serving the meal. Could have paced us better but didnt take anything off the quality of their sushi. Reserve your spot already.
Say you need a reservation and insist upon one when you get there even if they're entirely empty. Just bizarre
Very good sushi. Sayanora
Pretty good sushi with reasonable prices! This place is very small so reservations are highly recommended to avoid waiting.

Reservations are a MUST as the venue posts often that they are full up for the night with reservations. Sushi Capitol is an intimate venue with only a few tables which means you get excellent service. Plates are cleared as soon as you finish, you're never looking around for service as the soon as you look up with eye content they are at your table. While a quite venue and a great walkable location from the Metro or capitol area it does not have any outdoor seating like the location nearby. The sushi is spectacular and the use of real wasabi ground from the root has this place standing a head above other sushi spots in DC. The price is worth it if you appreciate high quality food and great service.
Small intimate in fresh small enough menu they can pick something and enjoy it very personable very welcoming
Best sushi I've had outside Japan.
I like the food a lot. It just take some time to wait for it.
Overpriced, mediocre sushi.

(Translated by Google) It is a level of sushi that even Japanese people will be satisfied with. The store is small and it seems better to make a reservation.  (Original) 日本人が食べてもなかなか満足できるレベルの寿司です。店構えは小さめで、予約をした方がよさそうです。

Really great sushi restaurant. Doesn't feel trendy or flashy but it has it where it counts. Really fresh fish, especially the Omakase, great beer and sake selection. This is definitely worth the drive.  Would definitely go back.
I wish I could rate this with more than 5 stars! Service was awesome, and the omakase was an absolute STEAL. Highly, highly recommend!
Great customer service but after waiting almost a year to get in and all the great reviews I found the sushi basically average.
Quality sushi and great service.
I'm vegetarian and they were very accommodating. Their vegetable roll is really favorable. They only get 4 stars because of how pricey they are! Went there at lunch and no specials.
Great food pleasant place
Was great experience
Came here for a dragon and florida roll. The dragon was decent but the florida roll just edible, nothing stood out. Its a nice, intimate place but the sushi is just very average.

I have visited every possible sushi place in the area. My wife and I consistently come to Sushi Capitol, because it has, by far, the freshest sushi in town. The place is extremely small, so I would highly recommend reserving prior to arriving here. I would also make sure that you ask the chef on what's special that day. Sometimes they will have fish, that you can not get elsewhere.  I would recommend coming here with an open mind, and when you come here, you will most certainly have a great meal.  UPDATE: Sushi quality fell a little. Not as fresh as it used to be. Otherwise,  not a bad place.
Put shrimp head in miso soup, service was not great and sushi didn't taste very good

fairly disgusted with this establishment. my boyfriend and I were visiting from out of town and heard rave reviews about the omakase option and wanted to splurge. we sat at the counter to enjoy the preparation and are very glad we did. the young gentleman helping the main chef was seen standing there looking bored and CLEANING HIS NAILS / CUTTING HIS CUTICLE with the knife. he looked up and noticed that my bf and I were looking at him and immediately stopped. he made no attempt to clean the knife or change it out.  We’re thankful we saw this before we were served any food. We told the waiter what we saw and that we wanted to leave. He said he would take care of it but at this point we both lost our appetite and excused ourselves from the restaurant. if you DO decide to go here, sit at the bar and make sure the chefs behind the counter are not using their cutlery to give themselves a manicure.  a negative star rating would be too kind.
A hidden gem in Capitol Hill
Well this is a little overdue. Was super thrilled to be able to get to eat here for diner on a trip. Hands down this omakase is amazing. Everything was delicious. Wish we had one in Chicago.

Other than the smell of this place, it was great! I was immediately disturbed by the odor which I was told by our waiter was the smell of sushi... I'm familiar with the smell of sushi and that it was not. The hostess then explained that a neighboring space sometimes gives off an odor that wafts in. Had it not been for her answer, we would have left.
Excellent sushi

For those interested in the omakase it costs $50 and my experience included: -Amusements of the day (See photo - Tempura fried shrimp head, raw oyster with shoyu, tender octopus, salmon sashimi) -12 pieces of nigiri (served in 2 sets of 6) -Handroll with toro  Everything was prepared and presented expertly. It was a quick in and out process as traditional sushi counters are. The fish served for the omakase was very standard. Having heard Sushi Capitol being dubbed "Best sushi in DC" I expected more extravagant offerings. Also, the manner in which the chef handled the fish was not delicate, as it usually is.  To summarize, a great omakase value but not life changing.
Rude, snotty, pretty decent fish.
Amazing!
First class service,  5 ☆, 5◇ , fresh catch daily fish, it's small place so you have to make reservations ahead.
Great location with good sushi. The staff is very friendly
Such delicious food - I've been missing the good life.
The sushi selection is wonderful, and the quality is upper middle tier.

So after years of hearing about and wanting to try this place I finally did and was happy I did. Small space, not cute or pretty or trendy just tables, chairs and some seats at the sushi bar. Because it is popular calling ahead and making a reservation is highly recommended. Going in blind my date and I ordered off the sushi menu which was a mistake since we quickly realized everyone else was doing the Chef's Tasting, which for $50 bucks you get a few courses of dishes including sushi you can't order off the menu. While everything we ordered was delicious, we missed out because the sushi going out for the tastings looked amazing. Oh well, now we know what to do the next time we go, and we will be going again!
Meh. Could have been a fluke but fish was not good cuts. Tough, like not Sushi grade.
The Chef Special is an excellent choice. Highly recommend.
Excellent quality sushi and reasonably priced. Pleasant service.
Satisfying!
Perfect sushi
Fantastic spot! If you're in D.C. and craving sushi - it's a must go-place!
Great sushi.  Omakase is worth it.
No question about it - this is the best sushi in town, your taste buds will explode when dining at this traditional sushi joint. Order the Omakase if you can for the best foody experience.
You've no doubt heard it before, but get the omakase.
I was born and raised in Tokyo,  and this is the best sushi you can get outside of Japan, hands down.
Best sushi in town with reasonable prices
Nice but cramped.
Very good moderate priced sushi
A bit expensive. Good quality fish. Makis are so so. No dessert. Probably won't be back.
Amazing sushi and service. The staff are friendly and smart.
Came here while waffling from the Capitol. Head avocado roll, fried tofu and seaweed  salad.  Everything was super tasty and the staff was  friendly and polite. Would totally do it again.
Excellent rice and sushi! Traditional yet absolutely delicious.

The chef's choice is quite tasty. Many delicate flavors and outstanding fish selection. You won't be disappointed by the fish: chef is an expert and what he creates is world class.  However, they could work on beverage pairing. I had a very bold IPA and it overwhelmed the sushi. The young, attractive waitresses could use more training as well. It reminded me of L.A. very much.

Best sushi I've had in the DC area. The chef choice is the way to go. Not too expensive. Great informative friendly staff. My cousin said he could taste the happiness in the food. The whole meal was great. Highly suggest
Small, authentic, great environment.  If you're adventurous, let the chef make your picks for you.
Cozy, great service, and very fresh tasting fish
(Translated by Google) It smells really bad  (Original) Huele muy mal

Best sushi I've had in DC so far. Which is more and indictment of the other places I've tried but this place isn't bad. I'm just surprised that I've had better in smaller cities across the country versus a major city like DC.

It was not particularly busy when we visited, but service was slow and it took 30 minutes to receive our food.  Service was polite, but slow.  They put wasabi on all their sushi without letting you know ahead of time. You can ask for sushi without wasabi already on it, but if you already got a whole bunch of sushi, without knowing there is already a bunch of wasabi on it, you are out of luck.  Sushi was alright, people in DC must have low standards to think this place is good. The ootoro was chewy, which is not good. First time I had chewy ootoro in my life.  Salmon was good. All in all, our experience was ruined by them not warning us ahead of time about pre-flavoring their sushi with wasabi.
Amazing sushi! Just be aware the peace it's Tony and they don't have any soda or juice. That said, GREAT 🍣.

The food was as good as others had praised. But the service was exceptional!! The chef behind the bar even made me something despite having everything put away for the evening (I didn't know, seriously). Made it anyway. Top tier service!!
Great local atmosphere, great sushi and friendly staff!
Simply marvelous best toro in all DMV

I've been to Sushi Capitol a few times - it can be a nice stop for lunch. There can be a wait, but they do take reservations to avoid that. Most recently, we treated friends to a birthday dinner here, and we all got the omakase (chef's choice). It was phenomenal. It involved small bites prior to a large boat of nigiri, and finishing with hand rolls.  Everything was great here.
Good quality sushi...incredibly fresh.  I highly recommend the chef's tasting menu.  Staff are attentive and polite.
Very small, low key sushi joint. Fish was fresh and quite good. Sake selection could be improved, but prices are very reasonable. Definitely make a reservation before heading over.

So happy to have this gem in the neighborhood. Great traditional sushi, good prices, friendly staff, and not impossible (yet) to get a last minute reservation most nights. One of my favorites in the city--good enough that I usually choose it over cheapy options and not so expensive that I can't be a regular.
Get the wasabi, get all the wasabi you can here, eat it plain. It is that good. This is the best kind of sushi restaurant, small, great service, great fish. Also, solid beer selection.

Worth the price! Their incredible selection of fish will leave you wanting to eat here every time you crave sushi. I enjoyed the experience so much I didn't even think about photographing my food. They had a great selection of beers as well. Make a reservation before you go!
Expensive but worth it. Considerate service, good variety, with something always special in the Sushi Special. Book way ahead if eating in, but the trick is to order takeout.

Definitely the best sushi you can get in the DC area. The chef puts great care into the fish he purchases. The prices are also great but this review would be the same if they were higher. Great deal for the omakase too. Definitely worth a shot! Just make sure to get a reservation (by calling the number on their website - no open table) as it gets busy here and is tough to get a seat without one.

I've lived near Capitol Sushi for years now and walk down Pennsylvania Ave countless of times and I never once have noticed this restaurant. Every Monday, one of my buddies and I meet up for dinner and this week we decided to try something new as you can only go to Sweet Green and Good Stuff so many times (or can you?). We walked in and the restaurant is pretty small and narrow with only a few tables but the place can turn out some regulars so you know it is good. The sushi was great! Perfectly put together and some of the best in DC that I've had. The service was great and fast. We'll be back for sure!
My favorite sushi spot. The yellow tail jaw and sushi quality and variety really make this stand out.
Cute little sushi place.  The fish was all fresh, delicious and very tasty.  Great lunch.

We are big fans of sashimi, and for us Sushi Capitol has the best sashimi grade fish.  The menu includes a daily selection of Japanese fish not seen anywhere else.  We have taken two Japanese friends here and they say this is the best selection and quality they have had in DC.  We agree, the spicy rolls are not spicy enough, but there enough special items on the changing menu to keep up surprises and interest.
Best sushi ive had my entire life highly recommend it to sushi lovers everywhere

Trust me: go here. I never write reviews but this is by far the best sushi I have ever had. Every roll we ate was amazing. It really lived up to the hype. Pro tip: make a reservation. They only have about 6 tables and a bar to sit at.

I'm from Seattle, where the sushi is amazingly fresh. This is by far the freshest, most amazing sushi I've ever had. Everything is perfect, even the edamame is the best I've ever had. You have to make reservations, even for a weeknight because the place is so small. Other than that, you've found your new favorite sushi restaurant!!!

Best Sushi I've ever had!!  The eel rolls are phenomenal and so is the shrimp tempura.  Cozy place, easy access to metro and capitol hill area.  Perfect for lunch or dinner.  I've spent the last year in DC and haven't found a better sushi place.
I prefer Kushi. If it makes a difference, I'm a Chirashi type. Nothing fancy... BUT I must add that the grated ginger was excellent!! Best I've ever had.

So good!! Good sushi in DC is nearly impossible to find. This place was delicious. The fish was so fresh. We had a wide assortment of nigiri and rolls. Highlights for me were the fatty tuna, red snapper, and salmon nigiri. The spicy tuna and shrimp tempura rolls were also very good. I'll definitely be back here again.

I have tried sushi from NYC to the Tsukiji fish market in Japan. This is hands down the best sushi I have had in DC. I have been here 3 times now and have tried their chirashi, omakase and sushi a la carte. The fish is always fresh from the regular salmon, yellowtail, toro to specials of the night like live scallop, uni, giant clam, eel and etc. The chef and manager always took the time to explain about the specials and what's in season. I had different uni every time I visited, from the east coast, Japan and California. During my last visit, as I noticed the difference in taste, the chef explained that it is difficult to get quality uni from Japan in the summer but  they should return in early fall. This is not a place to get those crazy rolls drenched in crunchy flakes and mayos typically seen at most Japanese restaurants in the area. It's one of the few authentic sushi restaurants and is a true gem. $50 for omakase is a great deal and you will not be disappointed.
He actually fresh grates wasabi root on a traditional sharkskin pallet for every order! LOVE.

Nice ambiance and good service.  Sushi ranged from OK (salmon that wasn't uber fresh, spicy tuna hand roll that wasn't at all spicy) to very good (unagi).  Tap water tasted funny and food portions (ohitashi and chicken karaage) were small, especially for the prices.
